attributedString.string: Celebrate Halloween with a musical ode to Harry Potter filled with actors, dancers, and magic with the Spokane Symphony. Experience music from Harry Potter…

words: Dress in costume and enjoy the pre-concert activities. Choose from matinee and evening performances. Pre-concert activities in the lobby begin 90 minutes before each show.

John Williams — “Hedwig’s Theme” from Harry Potter and the Sorcerer’s Stone
Patrick Doyle — “The Black Lake” from Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire 
Hans Peter Preu — Das Glasmännlein
Patrick Doyle — “Golden Egg (First Task)” from Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire 
John Powell — How to Train Your Dragon 
Igor Stravinsky — “Infernal Dance of King Kashchei”  from The Firebird 
John Williams — “Harry’s Wondrous World” from Harry Potter and the Sorcerer’s Stone
John Williams / arr. Jerry Brubaker — Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire (Concert Suite)  
Patrick Doyle / ed. James Shearman — "Harry in Winter" and “The Quidditch World Cup” from Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire 
Michael Giacchino — “Fiesta Espectacular” from Coco
Nicholas Hooper — “Fireworks” from Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix
V.I.P. tickets are available for these concerts and include swag bag, scarf and a private magic show with Nick Norton from Silverwood one hour and 15 minutes before the concert.

Tickets for this concert may be purchased with personalized service at the Box Office of Martin Woldson Theater at The Fox, 1001 West Sprague Avenue, or by calling 509-624-1200. They are also available online and at all TicketsWest outlets. ● BUY TICKETS

Martin Woldson Theater at The Fox stands behind www.TicketsWest.com as the only Internet site licensed to sell tickets for performances held at Martin Woldson Theater at The Fox. No other site has been authorized by Martin Woldson Theater at The Fox to sell, re-sell, or auction tickets.

Celebrate Halloween with a musical ode to Harry Potter filled with actors, dancers, and magic with the Spokane Symphony. Experience music from Harry Potter and the Sorcerer’s Stone, Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire, and Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix, along with other seasonal selections performed by the orchestra.
